Game engine as Vulkan practice

Dependencies are rather minimal;
 -Vulkan compatible GPU with up-to-date drivers
 -C17 (bug fix version of C11) compatible version of GCC
 -X11 XCB headers for window creation
 -Vulkan headers for core renderer
 -GLSL compiler for shader compilation

Assuming you are on an up-to-date system, you can get the dependencies as such:
 Arch / Manjaro / Antergos:
  sudo pacman -S libxcb vulkan-devel

 Fedora / CentOS / RHEL:
  sudo dnf install libxcb-devel vulkan-headers vulkan-validation-layers spirv-tools

 Debian / Ubuntu / Elementary / Mint:
  sudo apt-get install libx11-xcb-dev libvulkan-dev vulkan-validationlayers-dev spirv-tools

 Solus:
  sudo eopkg install system.devel libxcb vulkan-headers vulkan-validation-layers spirv-tools

And to compile and execute the engine, simply run:
 make
 ./engine.o

Currently following https://vulkan-tutorial.com/
Special thanks to the tutorial's creators and contributors
